          xCc: '',
          xBcc: '',
          xFolder: '\\Sara_Shackleton_Dec2000_June2001_1\\Notes Folders\\Argentina',
          xOrigin: 'SHACKLETON-S',
          xFileName: 'sshackle.nsf',
          body: '---------------------- Forwarded by Brent Hendry/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT on\n03/08/99 03:26 PM ---------------------------\n\n\nPablo Acevedo\n03/08/99 07:22 PM\n\nTo:   Federico Cerisoli/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Julian\nPoole/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT\ncc:   Brent Hendry/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT\nSubject:  MSA Perez\n\nReceived a call from Perez lawyer, Javier Casal, saying that they have been \noccupying most of their time in another priority Project and this is why they \nare delayed with their answer on the MSA proposal. He said that they have \nscheduled an internal meeting for next Monday, Aug. 9 to tackle this MSA with \nEnron Corp. and they will contact us asap with their comments.\n\nI told Perez that it was not worth while to delay it further than one more \nmonth. Casal answered that he took resposability for taking care of this \nmatter.\n\nkeep you posted.\n\nPablo',
          path: 'mock\\maildir\\folder-4\\argentina\\14_',
          mainFolder: '',
        },
        {
          messageId: '<17446022.1075844447559.JavaMail.evans@thyme>',
          date: 'Fri, 20 Aug 1999 01:29:00 -0700 (PDT)',
          from: 'dale.neuner@enron.com',
          to: 'julian.poole@enron.com, don.black@enron.com, brent.hendry@enron.com, sara.shackleton@enron.com, don.black@enron.com',
          cc: 'jefferson.sorenson@enron.com',
          bcc: 'jefferson.sorenson@enron.com',
          subject: 'Re: ISDA',
          xFrom: 'Dale Neuner',
          xTo: 'Julian Poole, Don Black, Federico Cerisoli@Enron, Brent Hendry, Sara Shackleton, Don Black',
          xCc: 'Jefferson D Sorenson',
          xBcc: '',
          xFolder: '\\Sara_Shackleton_Dec2000_June2001_1\\Notes Folders\\Argentina',
          xOrigin: 'SHACKLETON-S',
          xFileName: 'sshackle.nsf',
          body: 'I agree with Julian\'s explanation. We should not consider anything a \'done \ndeal\' until we receive the notification from trading and and deal is booked \nas a live trade.\n\nIn the interin, I\'ll become familiar with the deal terms.\n\nDale\n\n\n\n\n\nJulian Poole@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT\n08/19/99 06:42 PM\nTo: Tana Jones/HOU/ECT@ECT\ncc: Don Black/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Federico \nCerisoli/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Brent \nHendry/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Sara Shackleton/HOU/ECT@ECT, Dale \nNeuner/HOU/ECT@ECT \nSubject: Re: ISDA  \n\nTana,\n\nRegarding the proposed deal, the attached file describes the terms agreed \nupon with Duke (similar structure than C. Puerto\'s swap, except that now \nEnron sells & Duke buys). Duke\'s trader with whom I have been talking to is \nAmy Statler, located in their BsAs office.\nAfter reading the e-mail below sent by Erik Ludtke, from Duke, in which he \nmentions "ISDA agreement, partially executed by ECT.", and later requests the \nconfirmation letter, I still have my doubts on what Confirmation Letter he\'s \ntalking about. I think he\'s referring to the receipt letter for the ISDA \ndocument they sent and not the Confirm of this particular deal. Prior to this \nConfirm, we would need an ECT trader to get on the phone with Duke and \nexecute the deal.\n\nLet me know what you think and the outcome of your conversation with Roni \nCappadonna.\n\n\n\nThanks, Julian\n\n\n\nTo: Julian Poole/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Don \nBlack/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Federico \nCerisoli/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Brent \nHendry/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Sara Shackleton/HOU/ECT@ECT, Dale \nNeuner/HOU/ECT@ECT\ncc:  \nSubject: Re: ISDA\n\nSo far as much as I\'ve been able to track, the Houston Confirmation Desk does \nnot know about this Duke Confirm yet.  Don, can you contact Dale Neuner on \nthe Confirmation Desk ASAP with the proposed deal terms so he can prepare the \nConfirm and get it sent over to Duke.  Thanks!\n---------------------- Forwarded by Tana Jones/HOU/ECT on 08/19/99 02:28 PM \n---------------------------\nFrom: "Julian Poole/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT" AT ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@CCMAIL on \n08/19/99 06:44 PM\nTo: Tana Jones@ECT\ncc: Sara Shackleton@ECT, Federico Cerisoli AT ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@CCMAIL, "Don \nBlack/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT" AT ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@CCMAIL, Brent Hendry AT \nENRON_DEVELOPMENT@CCMAIL \nSubject: Re: ISDA\n\n\n\n\nTana, do you know what\'s the "Confirmation Letter" Duke is talking about in \nthe e-mail below? They are requesting us to send it to them.\n\nJulian\n---------------------- Forwarded by Julian Poole/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT on\n19/08/99 14:40 ---------------------------\n\n\nFederico Cerisoli\n19/08/99 19:43\n\nTo:   "Erik Ludtke" <elludtke@duke-energy.com>\ncc:   "Roni A Cappadonna" <vacappadonna@duke-energy.com>, "Alejandro Felices" \n<axfelices@duke-energy.com>, Don Black/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, \nSara Shackleton@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Brent \nHendry/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Julian\nPoole/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT\nSubject:  Re: ISDA\n\nGood!  I hope this is the first of a number of transactions we enter into \ntogether.   Please have your people sending the ISDA back to our lawyers in \nHouston with Duke\'s signature so we then complete the loop.\n\nJulian, would you please co-ordinate asap with our Houston staff to have them \nsending the confirmation to Roni at the fax number below?  Thanks.\n\n\n\n\n\n"Erik Ludtke" <elludtke@duke-energy.com> on 08/19/99 10:07:36 AM\n\nTo:   Federico Cerisoli/ENRON_DEVELOPMENT@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT\ncc:   "Carol F. Graebner" <cfgraebner@duke-energy.com>, "Amy J Statler" \n<ajstatler@duke-energy.com>, "Roni A Cappadonna" \n<vacappadonna@duke-energy.com>, "Alejandro Felices" \n<axfelices@duke-energy.com>, "Maria Zocchi" <mzocchi@duke-energy.com>\n\nSubject:  ISDA\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are in receipt of the ISDA agreement, partially executed by ECT.\n\nWe would like for ECT to send the confirmation letter to Roni Cappadonna in \nHouston, at 713-627-4778.  The fax number is 713-627-6524.',
