        {
          messageId: '<29166169.1075844447813.JavaMail.evans@thyme>',
          date: 'Wed, 24 Nov 1999 00:20:00 -0800 (PST)',
          from: 'lynn.aven@enron.com',
          to: 'brent.hendry@enron.com, don.black@enron.com',
          cc: '',
          bcc: '',
          subject: 'Tax Implications of Choice of Entity for Argentina Financial Trading',
          xFrom: 'Lynn Aven',
          xTo: 'Sara Shackleton@ENRON_DEVELOPMENT, Brent Hendry, Don Black',
          xCc: '',
          xBcc: '',
          xFolder:
            '\\Sara_Shackleton_Dec2000_June2001_1\\Notes Folders\\Argentina - financial trading',
          xOrigin: 'SHACKLETON-S',
          xFileName: 'sshackle.nsf',
          body: 'The attached chart summarizes the tax implications of the various options for \nchoice of legal entity for financial trading in Argentina.    The chart \naddressed income taxes only.  Moving the operations to Brazil will result in \nadditional transactions taxes that are not addressed  in this analysis.  As \nyou can see, the tax impact of each option depends the specific set of facts \nas to how Enron is operating its trading activity.  Of particular importance \nis the concept  that the US will tax the earnings of foreign jurisdictions \neven if there are no US employees involved in the transactions to the extent \na US affiliate of Enron is deemed to be providing substantial assistance to \nthe foreign entity that is involved in the financial trading activities.  \n\nThe current structure for financial trading in Argentina is the most tax \nefficient based upon the way Enron has chosen to conduct its business.  The \nearnings are limited to a single layer of tax in the US.  To the extent that \nthe Sao Paulo office develops into an operation that can fully support all \ntrading activity so that there is no support from the US, we may be able to \nrestructure the operations to provide more flexibility to the traders in \nSouth America.  Even if we shift the activity to a Brazilian entity,  the \ntraders will have to follow guidelines to avoid taxation in Argentina as well.\n\nLynn',
          path: 'mock\\maildir\\folder-4\\argentina___financial_trading\\4_',
          mainFolder: '',
        },
